  "technicalDetails": "<blockquote><strong>VFX</strong></blockquote><ul><li><strong>Laser Niagara system</strong> (NS_Laser)</li><li>Customizable <strong>Color, Width</strong> and <strong>End Point</strong></li></ul><p><br /></p><blockquote><strong>Reflection system</strong></blockquote><ul><li>Follows the <strong>law of reflection</strong>, preserving the incident angle relative to the surface normal.</li><li>Easy <strong>TAG</strong> implementation on any ACTOR or COMPONENT (&#34;<strong>REFLECT</strong>&#34;)</li></ul><p><br /></p><blockquote><strong>Refraction system</strong></blockquote><ul><li>Governed by <strong>Snell’s Law</strong>, the laser beam adjusts its trajectory when encountering glass, water, or other mediums.</li><li>Adjustable <strong>Refraction index</strong> parameter and Material detection</li><li>Easy <strong>TAG</strong> implementation on any ACTOR or COMPONENT (&#34;<strong>REFRACT</strong>&#34;)</li></ul><p><br /></p><blockquote><strong>Detection system</strong></blockquote><ul><li><strong>Specific Actor</strong> detection on<strong> cast</strong> or <strong>reference</strong></li><li>Detects Actor through reflection and refraction</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Number of Blueprints: 3 Lasers, 1 Demo</p><p>Input: Keyboard and Mouse</p><p>Network Replicated: Yes</p><p>Supported Development Platforms: Windows, Mac, Linux</p><p>Documentation: Every Blueprint has step-by-step comments about utility, demo level included</p>",
